    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION, TANDEM AXLES: SPICER J400-S, W460-S - DISASSEMBLE - OUTPUT SHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>OUTPUT SHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400436">Figure 36</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1400436" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1400436" filename="../figg14/G1400436.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 36. Output Shaft Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove rear drive shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove output shaft and cage from forward axle housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount output shaft in vise by clamping yoke in jaws of vise.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen end nut and remove nut and yoke (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400437">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400437" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400437" filename="../figg14/G1400437.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Remove End Nut and Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use snap ring tool to remove snap ring from bearing retainer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400438">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400438" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400438" filename="../figg14/G1400438.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Remove Snap Ring From Bearing Retainer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bearing and retainer from shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400439">Figure 39</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400439" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400439" filename="../figg14/G1400439.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. Remove Bearing and Retainer From Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a suitable sleeve to support bearing inner race, press bearing from shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable sleeve to press seal from retainer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean and inspect all components. Replace all worn or damaged components with genuine Spicer
                replacement parts.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
